": "2020-03-27T16:54:56Z", "closed_at": "2020-03-27T16:54:56Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I expected the read_line function to block the thread until i press enter on my keyboard.\r\nWith `cargo run` (I think that is debug) everything is fine, but with `cargo build --release | target\\release\\myprog` the read_line function seems not to block the thread?\r\n\r\nWindows 10\r\n`cargo 1.42.0 (86334295e 2020-01-31)`\r\n`rustc 1.42.0 (b8cedc004 2020-03-09)`\r\n`rustup 1.21.1 (7832b2ebe 2019-12-20)`\r\n\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nloop {\r\n    println!(\"Type 'exit' to terminate the program:\");\r\n    let mut input: String = String::new();\r\n    let _length = std::io::stdin().read_line(&mut input);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen:\r\n1. print message\r\n2. block until enter is pressed\r\n3. repeat\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened:\r\nwith `cargo run` => exactly what I expected\r\nwith `cargo build --release | target\\release\\myprog` => message is printed over and over again\r\n\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "Amityville-DE", "id": 9155156, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjkxNTUxNTY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9155156?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE", "html_url": "https://github.com/Amityville-DE", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amityville-DE/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.gith